# Default dev proxy: `/api` → local Node on :8080 (same browser origin as Vite → login/session works).
# From repo root run in another terminal: `npm run dev:server` (needs `server/.env`; see server/README.md).
# Or one command: `npm run dev:local` (installs root `concurrently` via `npm install` at repo root first).
#
# Do NOT point this file at production Render for day-to-day dev: the hosted API rejects
# `Origin: http://localhost:*` on cookie POSTs (`FORBIDDEN_ORIGIN`). Use the deployed web app for cloud testing.
#
# If you still need to hit Render for a one-off, use gitignored `.env.development.local` only — expect login to fail.
VITE_API_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:8080
VITE_RECIPE_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:8080
